{"id":82909,"date":"2022-06-30T12:32:52","date_gmt":"2022-06-30T10:32:52","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/?p=82909"},"modified":"2022-09-25T13:22:36","modified_gmt":"2022-09-25T11:22:36","slug":"tatacoa-desert","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/colombia\/tatacoa-desert\/","title":{"rendered":"Tatacoa Desert: Colombia&#8217;s Best Kept Secret"},"content":{"rendered":"<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"todo\">5 Things to do in Tatacoa Desert<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tatacoa Desert consists of two parts, the red and grey desert, which can both be explored within a day. It is also one of the warmest places in Colombia, with a 35-degree average temperature. However, there is heavy rainfall in the area throughout April and May, resulting in a greener desert. For this reason, it is technically not a desert.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--mustread \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--mustread\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p>Also see: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/colombia\/colombia-itinerary\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Ultimate 3-week Colombia Itinerary (Travel Guide)<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29104359\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-9.jpg\" alt=\"red desert hike tatacoa colombia\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" alt=