t__image-wrap\"><img src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29153329\/1-tatacoa-desert-colombia-19x30.jpg\" data-src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29153329\/1-tatacoa-desert-colombia-376x600.jpg\" class=\"lazyload block-pinterest__image\" alt=\"Tatacoa Desert: Colombia&#x2019;s Best Kept Secret\" height=\"600\" width=\"376\">\n                    <\/div>\n                <\/div>\n            <\/a>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-5-stargazing-in-tatacoa-desert\">5. Stargazing in Tatacoa Desert<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Because of its remote location and undiscovered nature, there is barely any light pollution in the Tatacoa Desert. This makes it one of the best places in South America to go stargazing. Visit the observation tower (<a href=\"https:\/\/goo.gl\/maps\/aWoUgfEsXv7TyXSP9\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">here<\/a>) for an explanation and a look through one of six enormous telescopes. When the conditions are perfect, you should be able to see the galaxy with the naked eye. Full moon and clouds can all make it extremely difficult to see the stars.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--attractions \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--attractions\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p>The entrance fee to the observation tower + tour is 10.000 COP.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25.jpg\" alt=\"Stargazing Tatacoa Desert\"><\/noscript><img width=\"250\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Stargazing Tatacoa Desert\" class=\"wp-image-84611 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1418px) 100vw, 1418px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25.jpg 1418w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-443x600.jpg 443w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-598x810.jpg 598w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-250x338.jpg 250w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-22x30.jpg 22w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-120x163.jpg 120w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-133x180.jpg 133w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-567x768.jpg 567w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-756x1024.jpg 756w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-798x1080.jpg 798w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-1064x1440.jpg 1064w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-300x406.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-600x812.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-150x203.jpg 150w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25-22x30.jpg\" src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29143154\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-25.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2 id=\"hotels\">Where to Stay in the Tatacoa Desert<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>There are two areas where you can spend the night: the Tatacoa Desert or <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/hotels-all-villavieja\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Villavieja<\/a> (a small town close to the desert). We recommend spending at least one night, ideally two, in Tatacoa because it&#x2019;s a time-consuming destination to reach.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--hotels\">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--hotels\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/tatacoa-hotels-all\/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Here are all your hotel options in Tatacoa.<\/a><\/p>\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29102129\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-3.jpg\" alt=\"tatacoa desert Villavieja colombia\"><\/noscript><img width=\"226\" height=\"338\" a