><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you plan on walking or cycling, download Google Maps or Maps.me offline to not get lost in the desert. Also <strong>bring a lot of water<\/strong>, a hat, sunscreen and sunglasses because it can get extremely hot and bright.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h3 id=\"h-how-many-days-do-you-need\">How many days do you need?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>We recommend spending at least one night in the Tatacoa Desert. You need one full day from morning to evening to enjoy all the things to do in Tatacoa. Two nights would be ideal since you can split your journey over two days and also relax a little bit.&#xA0;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21.jpg\" alt=\"Xil&#xF3;palos Trail tatacoa colombia\"><\/noscript><img width=\"256\" height=\"338\" alt=\"Xil&#xF3;palos Trail tatacoa colombia\" class=\"wp-image-84600 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1454px) 100vw, 1454px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21.jpg 1454w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-454x600.jpg 454w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-613x810.jpg 613w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-256x338.jpg 256w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-23x30.jpg 23w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-123x163.jpg 123w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-136x180.jpg 136w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-582x768.jpg 582w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-775x1024.jpg 775w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-818x1080.jpg 818w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-1091x1440.jpg 1091w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-300x396.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-600x792.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-150x198.jpg 150w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21-23x30.jpg\" src=\"\/build\/images\/blank.png\" onerror=\"this.srcset='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.src='\/build\/images\/blank.png'; this.classList.remove('lazypreload'); \"><a class=\"pinit\" href=\"https:\/\/www.pinterest.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-pin=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29140707\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-21.jpg\">Save<\/a><\/div><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-can-you-do-a-day-trip-to-the-tatacoa-desert\">Can you do a day trip to the Tatacoa Desert?&#xA0;<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, it is possible to visit the Tatacoa Desert from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/hotels-all-neiva\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">the city of Neiva<\/a> on a day trip. You can fly from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/colombia\/things-to-do-bogota\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Bogota<\/a> to Neiva Airport and directly hop in a car to visit the desert, which is about 1 hour away from Neiva.&#xA0;(<a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/hotels-all-neiva\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Book your hotel in Neiva<\/a>)<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-group\"><div class=\"wp-block-group__inner-container\">\n<h2>Getting to the Tatacoa Desert in Colombia<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tatacoa Desert is an off-the-beaten-path destination and is quite time-consuming to reach. To get to the desert, you first have to travel to Neiva, a larger city with a bus station and domestic airport. Travel by bus in about 6-9 hours (<a href=\"https:\/\/saltinourhair.12go.asia\/en\/travel\/bogota\/neiva\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">book bus tickets here<\/a>) or 1 hour by plane from <a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/colombia\/things-to-do-bogota\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Bogota<\/a> (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/flights-bogota-neiva\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">book a flight here<\/a>). <\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you&#x2019;ve arrived in Neiva, you will need to take a taxi or bus (Colectivo) for about 1\/1.5 hour to get to your hotel in Villavieja or the Tatacoa Desert. We felt very safe and welcomed during our entire journey by the Colombian people.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"block-link block-link--flight \">\n                <div class=\"block-link__container\">\n\n                    <div class=\"salt-icon__container\">\n                        <span class=\"salt-icon salt-icon--flight\"><\/span>\n                        <svg class=\"icon icon-round-shape\"><use xlink:href=\"#icon-round-shape\"><\/use><\/svg>\n                    <\/div>\n\n                    <p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.saltinourhair.com\/go\/flights-bogota-neiva\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Book a flight to Neiva here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n                <\/div>\n            <\/div>\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div class=\"image-wrapper\"><div class=\"fake-image\"><\/div><noscript><img src=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus.jpg\" alt=\"bus tatacoa desert\"><\/noscript><img width=\"450\" height=\"327\" alt=\"bus tatacoa desert\" class=\"wp-image-84620 lazypreload\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\" data-srcset=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus.jpg 1920w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-800x581.jpg 800w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-1080x784.jpg 1080w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-450x327.jpg 450w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-30x22.jpg 30w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-163x118.jpg 163w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-248x180.jpg 248w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-768x558.jpg 768w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-1024x743.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-1440x1046.jpg 1440w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-300x218.jpg 300w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-600x436.jpg 600w, https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/06\/29144938\/tatacoa-desert-colombia-bus-150x109.jpg 150w\" tempsrc=\"https:\/\/static.saltinourhair.com\/wp-content\/